rComments: I don't know why he makes it harder than it should be. The group project was awful. The work was consuming time.

I have his class for three hours at night and each week, it is either doing a quiz on the chapters or submitting an assignment. The lecture material is pretty much reading-based. If you are looking for a less workload elective, I don't recommend taking it unless you're interested in reading and case studies.

One of Telfer's best teachers if not the best. He is available outside of class hours to answer your questions. His course is well explained and we learn a lot. Success guaranteed with this teacher.This is the kind of teacher that Telfer needs. If you put in a minimum of effort you will pass his course.
Easy class, teacher helped in making it accessible for us. Explains well, clear lectures, the exams aren't tricky. There are group works and quizzes but he makes good accommodations!
He comes off as a nice prof but isn't available for questions outside of class and tends to skip through the most important things in the course. I would definitely look for other options first.

One of the best profs I've ever had. Explains everything so well, takes time to talk to you outside of class if you ever need to, shows a lot of empathy towards students, and provides fair assessments. Quizzes are very easy, the simulation is a lot of work but Jasmin is happy to help - just ask! Very grateful to have had him teaching me.

Amazing to teach a very important class for business. It was not boring at all. He is very engaging and available whenever you need. For his part of the course, everything was laid out perfectly and fairly simple to follow along. For Intopia Simulation, it was stressful but out of his control, he checked in on us during the simulation as well :)
Jasmin is really caring. His classes are interactive, and you can't get bored with him. His exams reflect what we study in class. Just study and you'll be fine.
He's friendly and always ready to help. Good lectures.

This Prof is probably one of the best at Telfer. Extremely humble and is always willing to help. Always stays after class hours to answer students' questions. He makes the class extremely fun and encourages students to do better by giving feedback during Intopia.

Professor Manseau is a great lecturer and keeps students engaged. Participation is important, and you must come to class prepared. He is a fair marker, quizzes are easy, but serious effort is required for the cases and Intopia simulation. This was one of the best courses I have taken at Telfer. I strongly recommend!

My favourite prof in all of my university years so far! If I ever have the chance to take a class with him I 100% will! Classes are enjoyable and pass by quickly! everyone can finish with a good grade if you try!

The prof is great for animating his class. However, he mentioned it can be boring so you have to read your chapter before every class because you will have a quiz every time, then he will explain the chapter. As well, we have a case to do at the end of every class, so he can be tiring after a long day. You need the book, not everything on PowerP.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Great teacher, either quizzes or group work every class so be careful not to miss any (or to be prepared when you do)
Great teacher. Dynamic, fair.
Speaks very clearly, explains well, actually tells you what his midterms are about unlike other profs, good powerpoints
He speaks very fast so you need to be able to process things quickly His teaching isn't bad but sometimes it is a bit overcomplicated. He's not a bad professor and is readily able to help students.
Jasmin is a great prof ! Would highly recommend taking any class with him as he explains things extremely well and is very clear with his evaluation methods.
By far the best prof I've had in University. Take him.
Best prof I've had yet.
Very well prepared lectures and very engaging professor. 10 out of 10 would recommend!

It all depends on which class you take with him. I took decisions models (B+) with him.... don't do it! He talks way too fast to understand. THAT BEING SAID, I took entrepreneurship(A+) and strategic management(A+) with him and he was the best. He really cares about the student's success and, as an entrepreneur, has valuable experience to share.
Très bon prof! Beaucoup d'entregent et passionné de la matière qu'il enseigne. Relie beaucoup de leçon de vie au contenu enseigné.

You want to learn something useful in a class specific for entrepreneurship , he's the guy. He'll give you all the necessary stuff to build yourself up for the "beginning". I wish I took this class as soon as I could. The best learning advice I got. He will adapt the class according to the class needs.  You want a good tip, buy him a beer.

A class where you'll learn stuff in depth. No surprises during the exams. He'll give you a lot of examples in class on the questions you need more explanations. He'll adapt the class according to the class necessities. He gives the information quick, like it should be. God he's a master at Microsoft Excel.  Do your homework.
Bon prof et bon yable.  Toujours enthousiaste et il encourage grandement les étudiants à donner leur point de vue pour enrichir les discussions.
Really good teacher

The homeworks prepare you well, if you keep up in the class the material is fairely easy. Hes very enthusiastic and tends to go fast, but does recaps after or will slowdown if asked. Very good teacher in my opinion.
Very hard class in general, teacher makes it worse.

Talks very fast. Does not have scheduled office hours. Will help over e-mail and about 20mins before and after class. Will not treat you as stupid if you ask a question. Will not help you at the end of the semestre if you have never asked for help before so maybe ask him a couple questions a long the way just to make sure he will help at the end.
le prof le moins clair de Telfer, essayer d'éviter de l'avoir comme prof!

Probably the most unclear teacher I have ever had. He gets questions from the class and barely answer. No background as en entrepreneur and believe he knows everything. If you like business, you will hate this class. The only thing you will learn is the formal, obvious stuff. The things that actually makes you a better entrepreneur arent presented.

C'est un bon professeur, très inspirant et passionné par sa matière. Il est toujours là pour ses étudiants et n'hésite pas à répondre aux questions même s'il doit rester longtemps après le cours. Les travaux à rendre sont faisables mais ça demande des efforts. En gros, un bon cours mais pas le plus facile !

J'ai vraiment aimé le professeur, il essai de faire beaucoup d'exemples en classe ce qui aide beaucoup pour les devoirs et examens. Beaucoup de devoirs mais ils sont nécessaires afin de bien comprendre la matière (surtout la première partie du cours). Ces examens étaient relativement faciles et si vous etes capable de mettre la main sur un final des années précédentes, faites-le! Le final était exactement le même que celui que j'avais vu.

Le prof explique bien la matière, mais les devoirs à remettre à chaque semaine sont exigeants. Les examens étaient représentatifs et pas trop difficiles. Par contre, il prend longtemps à répondre aux courriels.

Les devoirs représentent l'examen. C'est un cours quand même facile si tu fais tes devoirs et des bonnes feuilles de notes. Le prof est toujours présent pour répondre aux questions. Un bon prof en général.

C'est un bon prof, il est toujours là pour répondre à nos questions et il aime répondre aux questions. Les devoirs représentent les examens. Il a souvent des touches d'humours lors de ses cours, tu vois qu'il est passionné par sa matière. Mais il y a des devoirs à remettre à chaque semaine et ils peuvent être exigent. Le prof est recommandé.
